maize-94: ls is plain-name listing (the -l long form deferred to maize-244).

Upstream file/function: ls.c (struct entry, mkent, indicator, printname, output,
entcmp, lsdir, visit, ls, main).
Why: the upstream long form (-l/-n) needs getpwuid/getgrgid (pwd.h/grp.h),
localtime/strftime (time.h), major/minor (sysmacros.h), readlink, and struct stat
st_atim/st_mtim/st_ctim timespec fields, none of which the Maize freestanding libc
provides yet; those enablers are filed as maize-244. This overlay reduces ls to
plain-name listing: the long-form output branch, the owner/group/time columns, the
timestamp entry field, and the symlink-target metadata are dropped rather than
faked. The -q non-printable filter (isprintrune -> libutf rune tables + bsearch) is
also deferred; printname writes names verbatim. -l/-n/-h/-c/-u/-t/-q are accepted
but list plain names (documented wave-1 deviation); name and -S size ordering plus
-a/-A/-1/-r/-R/-d/-F/-p/-i still work.
